quran[29]{c,v,t}:
  81,1,"When the sun shall be folded up,",footnotes:182594:1
  81,2,"when the stars shall scatter away,",footnotes:182595:1
  81,3,"when the mountains shall be set in motion,",footnotes:182596:1
  81,4,"when the ten-months pregnant camels shall be abandoned,",footnotes:182597:1
  81,5,"when the savage beasts shall be brought together,",footnotes:182598:1
  81,6,"when the seas shall be set boiling,",footnotes:182599:1
  81,7,"when the souls shall be rejoined (with their bodies),",footnotes:182600:1|182601:2
  81,8,"and when the girl-child buried alive shall be asked:"
  81,9,"for what offence was she killed?",footnotes:182602:1
  81,10,"and when the scrolls of (men's) deeds shall be unfolded,"
  81,11,"and when Heaven is laid bare;",footnotes:182603:1
  81,12,"and Hell is stoked,"
  81,13,"and Paradise brought nigh:",footnotes:182604:1
  81,14,"then shall each person know what he has brought along."
  81,15,"No indeed; I swear by the alternating stars",footnotes:182605:1
  81,16,"that hide,"
  81,17,"and by the night as it recedes,"
  81,18,"and the morn as it breathes.",footnotes:182606:1
  81,19,"Verily this is the word of a noble message-bearer;",footnotes:182607:1
  81,20,"one mighty and held in honour with the Lord of the Throne;",footnotes:182608:1
  81,21,"there he is obeyed and held trustworthy.",footnotes:182609:1|182610:2
  81,22,"(O people of Makkah), your companion is not mad;",footnotes:182611:1
  81,23,"he indeed saw the message-bearer on the clear horizon;",footnotes:182612:1
  81,24,"nor does he grudge (conveying this knowledge about) the Unseen;",footnotes:182613:1
  81,25,"nor is it a word of an accursed Satan.",footnotes:182614:1
  81,26,"Where to are you then heading?"
  81,27,"It is nothing but Good Counsel for everyone in the world,"
  81,28,"for everyone of you who wishes to follow the Straight Way;",footnotes:182615:1
  81,29,"but your wishing will not avail unless Allah, the Lord of the Universe, so wishes.",footnotes:182616:1
